Pivot Limits

Or really, limiting results based on secondary queries.

Let's suppose we wanted to look flight data but only at only the top 5 carriers and only the top 5 destinations.

Carriers by destination produces 1958 rows 

query: flights -> {
  group_by:
    carriers.nickname
    destination_code
  aggregate: flight_count
}

SELECT 
   carriers_0.nickname as nickname,
   flights.destination as destination_code,
   COUNT( 1) as flight_count
FROM `malloy-data.faa.flights` as flights
LEFT JOIN `malloy-data.faa.carriers` AS carriers_0
  ON carriers_0.code=flights.carrier
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY 3 desc

Query for the top 5 carriers

Query to find the most interesting carriers.

query: flights -> {
  top: 5
  group_by: carriers.nickname
  aggregate: flight_count
}

SELECT 
   carriers_0.nickname as nickname,
   COUNT( 1) as flight_count
FROM `malloy-data.faa.flights` as flights
LEFT JOIN `malloy-data.faa.carriers` AS carriers_0
  ON carriers_0.code=flights.carrier
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 2 desc
LIMIT 5

Run all three queries together as Aggregating Subqueries.

Produces a table with a single row and three columns. Each column essentially contains a table

query: flights -> {
  nest: main_query is {
    group_by:
      carriers.nickname
      destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_carriers is {
    top: 5
    group_by: carriers.nickname
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_destinations is {
    top: 5
    group_by: destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
}

WITH __stage0 AS (
  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__3,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__3
  FROM `malloy-data.faa.flights` as flights
  LEFT JOIN `malloy-data.faa.carriers` AS carriers_0
    ON carriers_0.code=flights.carrier
  CROSS JOIN (SELECT row_number() OVER() -1  group_set FROM UNNEST(GENERATE_ARRAY(0,3,1)))
  GROUP BY 1,2,3,5,7
)
SELECT
  ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN STRUCT(
    nickname__1 as nickname, 
    destination_code__1 as destination_code, 
    flight_count__1 as flight_count
    ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__1 desc ) as main_query,
  ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN STRUCT(
    nickname__2 as nickname, 
    flight_count__2 as flight_count
    ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__2 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_carriers,
  ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN STRUCT(
    destination_code__3 as destination_code, 
    flight_count__3 as flight_count
    ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__3 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_destinations
FROM __stage0

Project the main query and use the top nested queries to limit the results

Project produces a cross join of the tables. The filter essentially does an inner join, limiting the main queries results to dimensional values that are produce in the filtering queries.

query: flights -> {
  nest: main_query is {
    group_by:
      carriers.nickname
      destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_carriers is {
    top: 5
    group_by: carriers.nickname
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_destinations is {
    top:5
    group_by: destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
} -> {
  where:
    main_query.nickname = top_carriers.nickname,
    main_query.destination_code = top_destinations.destination_code
  project: main_query.*
}

  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__1,

      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__3,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__3
  FROM `malloy-data.faa.flights` as flights
  LEFT JOIN `malloy-data.faa.carriers` AS carriers_0
    ON carriers_0.code=flights.carrier

  GROUP BY 1,2,3,5,7
)
, __stage1 AS (
  SELECT
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN STRUCT(
      nickname__1 as nickname, 
      destination_code__1 as destination_code, 
      flight_count__1 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__1 desc ) as main_query,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN STRUCT(
      nickname__2 as nickname, 
      flight_count__2 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__2 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_carriers,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN STRUCT(
      destination_code__3 as destination_code, 
      flight_count__3 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__3 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_destinations
  FROM __stage0
)
SELECT 
   main_query_0.nickname as nickname,
   main_query_0.destination_code as destination_code,
   main_query_0.flight_count as flight_count
FROM __stage1 as base
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.main_query) as main_query_0
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.top_carriers) as top_carriers_0
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.top_destinations) as top_destinations_0
WHERE (main_query_0.nickname=top_carriers_0.nickname)
AND (main_query_0.destination_code=top_destinations_0.destination_code)

Render the results as a pivot table 

query: flights -> {
  nest: main_query is {
    group_by:
      carriers.nickname
      destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_carriers is {
    top: 5
    group_by: carriers.nickname
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
  nest: top_destinations is {
    top:5
    group_by: destination_code
    aggregate: flight_count
  }
} -> {
  where:
    main_query.nickname = top_carriers.nickname and
    main_query.destination_code = top_destinations.destination_code
  group_by: main_query.nickname
  nest: destination_pivot is {
    project:
      main_query.destination_code
      main_query.flight_count
  }
}

WITH __stage0 AS (
  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      carriers_0.nickname
      END as nickname__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      flights.destination
      END as destination_code__3,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      COUNT( 1)
      END as flight_count__3
  FROM `malloy-data.faa.flights` as flights
  LEFT JOIN `malloy-data.faa.carriers` AS carriers_0
    ON carriers_0.code=flights.carrier
  CROSS JOIN (SELECT row_number() OVER() -1  group_set FROM UNNEST(GENERATE_ARRAY(0,3,1)))
  GROUP BY 1,2,3,5,7
)
, __stage1 AS (
  SELECT
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN STRUCT(
      nickname__1 as nickname, 
      destination_code__1 as destination_code, 
      flight_count__1 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__1 desc ) as main_query,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN STRUCT(
      nickname__2 as nickname, 
      flight_count__2 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__2 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_carriers,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN STRUCT(
      destination_code__3 as destination_code, 
      flight_count__3 as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  flight_count__3 desc  LIMIT 5) as top_destinations
  FROM __stage0
)
, __stage2 AS (
  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set=0 THEN
      main_query_0.nickname
      END as nickname__0,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=0 THEN STRUCT(
      main_query_0.destination_code as destination_code, 
      main_query_0.flight_count as flight_count
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  main_query_0.destination_code asc ) as destination_pivot__0
  FROM __stage1 as base
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.main_query) as main_query_0
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.top_carriers) as top_carriers_0
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(base.top_destinations) as top_destinations_0
  CROSS JOIN (SELECT row_number() OVER() -1  group_set FROM UNNEST(GENERATE_ARRAY(0,0,1)))
  WHERE (main_query_0.nickname=top_carriers_0.nickname)and(main_query_0.destination_code=top_destinations_0.destination_code)
  GROUP BY 1,2
)
SELECT
  nickname__0 as nickname,
  ANY_VALUE(CASE WHEN group_set=0 THEN destination_pivot__0 END) as destination_pivot
FROM __stage2
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 1 asc
